==English==
{{wikipedia|Ripening}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɹaɪpən/|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} to grow [[ripe]]; to become [[mature]], as in [[botany]]: grain, fruit, flowers, and the like; as, grapes ripen in the sun.
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To approach or come to perfection.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To cause to mature; to make ripe; as, the warm days  ripened the corn.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To mature; to fit or prepare; to bring to perfection; as, to ripen the [[judgment]].
#: ''When faith and love, which parted from thee never,       Had ripined thy iust soul to dwell with God. --Milton.''

